		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message27656389">A heartwarming film with the best cast of characters I've seen in any Satoshi Kon movie. Their differences in personalities and the similar situation they find themselves in allows for some highly unique and entertaining interactions between them as well as how easy they are to relate to. Their finding of the baby is accompanied by a sense of responsibility, not only in searching for the baby's parents and taking care of the baby but in confronting their own pasts as well. One of the problems I had is the ridiculous amount of coincidences present throughout the film, we see the characters randomly meeting others who just happen to have something to do with their backgrounds, especially when it's as simple as one of the main characters getting beat up and being taken care of by the other main character's parents while the same main character chooses to visit shortly after. Towards the end, everything also feels so fast paced and over-the-top as if the viewers were just expected to go along with it, even Miyuki's story felt a bit unresolved as well. The visuals and sound compliment the tone of the movie rather well for me to say that it's probably the best anime movie to watch during Christmas time. Overall, I think Tokyo Godfathers is a very pleasant watch that I would recommend to any anime fan due to its simplicity, probably making it the easiest Satoshi Kon work to get into.</div><div class="postActions"></div></td>
		</tr></table></div><div class="forum_boardrowspacer">&nbsp;</div>
