		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message27667363">A Christmas Classic, and in my opinion, a family-friendly film that audiences of all ages should enjoy. Satoshi Kon really shows off his flexibility as a director with this work, as it's very unlike his other pieces, yet still retains his unique style and direction. A beautiful story, through and through, and something that really hits you as a holiday film. Not just because it's snowing. Not in the same way that some people call Die Hard a Christmas movie (pfft). In the way that it encompasses everything that the spirit of Christmas represents. And I have a lot of respect for Kon's ability to do this with such aplomb.</div><div class="postActions"></div><div class="sig"><span style="font-size: 80%;"><div style="text-align: center;"><img class="userimg" data-src="http://fc06.deviantart.net/fs42/f/2009/096/7/8/Tonberry_Banner_by_Doaj.jpg" /><br />
Vengeance of everyone's grudge.<!--size--></span><!--center--></div><br />
"I didn't add it to my list so I forgot I was watching that." - lpf</div></td>
