		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message27835349">I feel the same way in that Tokyo Godfathers is considerably charming and authentic-feeling, and something you wouldn't really expect out of a Kon film. All the magical coincidences are absurd asspulls to save the drama, but it does suit the novelty of the film. Everything else is splendidly done, such as taking a quirky premise and following its story with enough excitement per meandered path. The characters also share enough of that spaz that you feel at home with the environment, and they each grow as individuals over time in very palpable methods. You wouldn't think that you could identify with a runaway, a crossdresser, or an alcoholic, but Tokyo Godfathers makes it happen in more ways than you can imagine.</div><div class="postActions"></div><div class="sig"><div style="text-align: center;"><!--link--><a href="http://myanimelist.net/clubs.php?cid=40791">QD</a><!--center--></div></div></td>
