		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message27844411">It's not only plot progression that is driven by conveniences and coincidences. It's also characterisation--we learn about the characters because they happen to run into so many people related to them (the daughter, the father, the conman, the other employees at the club) and other coincidences like finding the newspaper snippet telling the girl her dog's come back home... While all of that is touching, and I certainly do love the characters, I think the story would have been more credible in a TV series in which you can space out the coincidences and have some time skips if needed. (But if they did that, to be sure, there would be no more CHRISTMAS MIRACLE, which is part of why the film is so heartwarming!)</div><div class="postActions"></div></td>
