		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message27878163">The massive number of conveniences and coincidences is one of the strengths of the film.  Coincidence becomes almost atmospheric, and as the absurdity builds I find that it sweeps me along, and I'm laughing with it immediately and by the end I think I would have been surprised if any scene -didn't- somehow tie into one of the characters' pasts in a contrived way.  Unlike lpf I feel the pacing is perfect, and if the coincidences had been spaced out over a longer period of time the movie would have lost a lot of the effect.  The 'Christmas miracle' element is certainly present in the coincidences as well, which adds a heartwarming effect to the absurd/hilarious happenings.<br />
<br />
Maybe I just like silly things, but I find this to be Satoshi Kon's strongest film.</div><div class="postActions"></div><div class="sig"><div style="text-align: center;"><!--link--><a href="http://myanimelist.net/clubs.php?cid=2913"> <img src="http://i.imgur.com/Cci6bQq.png" /> </a><!--center--></div></div></td>
		</tr></table></div><div class="forum_boardrowspacer">&nbsp;</div>
